  <record id="ir_ui_view_3760" model="ir.ui.view">
    <field name="arch" type="xml">
      <t name="Appointment Types" track="1" t-name="website_appointment.appointments_cards_layout">
        <t t-call="website.layout">
          <div id="wrap" class="o_appointment_index">
            <div class="oe_structure"/>
            <t t-call="website_appointment.website_calendar_index"/>
            <t t-call="website_appointment.website_calendar_index_topbar"/>
            <div class="o_appointment_choice o_appointment_appointments_list">
              <div class="container">
                <div id="o_appointment_index_main_col" class="col-md px-0 o_wappointment_appointment_list_columns">
                  <div class="row row-gap-3">
                    <t t-call="website_appointment.appointments_cards"/>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="oe_structure oe_empty">
                <section class="s_faq_list pb64 o_colored_level pt48" data-snippet="s_faq_list" data-name="FAQ List">
                  <div class="container">
                    <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
                    <div class="row">
                      <div class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16 o_colored_level">
                        <h6>
                          <strong>How long does an escape room last?</strong>
                          <br/>
                        </h6>
                        <p>Each experience lasts a total of about 75 minutes — 60 minutes of gameplay, plus a short briefing before and debrief after. You’ll have a full hour inside the room to solve puzzles, uncover secrets, and make your escape.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16 o_colored_level">
                        <h6>
                          <strong>Do I need any special knowledge or skills to play?</strong>
                          <br/>
                        </h6>
                        <p>Not at all! Escape rooms are designed for all types of thinkers — no trivia, math skills, or outside knowledge required. Just bring curiosity, communication, and a willingness to think outside the box.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16 o_colored_level">
                        <h6>
                          <strong>Can we play with fewer players than the recommended minimum?</strong>
                          <br/>
                        </h6>
                        <p>You can, but keep in mind that fewer players means more puzzles per person! If you’re up for the challenge, it’s totally doable — just know that some tasks might take longer or require extra cleverness with a smaller group.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16 o_colored_level">
                        <h6>
                          <strong>Are your escape rooms scary?</strong>
                          <br/>
                        </h6>
                        <p>Only some of them. Each room has a different atmosphere — from mysterious to intense to suspenseful. <em>Specimen X</em>, for example, leans into the horror vibe, while <em>The Holmes Paradox</em> is more Sherlock than scream-fest. Scare level is marked on each room page.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16 o_colored_level">
                        <h6>
                          <strong>What happens if we don’t escape in time?</strong>
                          <br/>
                        </h6>
                        <p>No worries — most groups don’t! Our game master will step in when your time’s up and walk you through the remaining puzzles. You’ll still have a blast, and most of the fun is in the experience itself, not just the escape.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="col-lg-4 pt16 pb16 o_colored_level">
                        <h6>
                          <strong>Are your rooms suitable for kids or families?</strong>
                          <br/>
                        </h6>
                        <p>Absolutely! We welcome players of all ages, though some rooms have minimum age suggestions due to complexity or themes. <em>Curse of the Pharaoh</em> is a great pick for families and younger players. Just check the age limit listed for each room.</p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </section>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </t>
      </t>
    </field>
    <field name="key">website_appointment.appointments_cards_layout</field>
    <field name="name">Appointment Types</field>
    <field name="type">qweb</field>
    <field name="website_id" ref="website.default_website"/>
  </record>
